      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup reviewed by independent analyst; boundary conditions, material properties, and post-processing scripts verified against documented simulation plan.",
      "rationale": "Independent peer review of simulation setup performed by senior CFD engineer not involved in model development. Checklist of 38 items verified. Two minor discrepancies in turbulence intensity specification identified and corrected prior to production runs. Required level met."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis damage model selection justified with reference to literature benchmarks for rotating blood-contacting flows.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on published benchmarks for centrifugal blood pump flows (Hariharan et al. 2011, Pauli et al. 2014). Power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) applied with published constants. Model form uncertainty acknowledged as dominant source; sensitivity study performed. Required level met."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Sensitivity analysis performed for key uncertain inputs (viscosity, hematocrit, damage model constants); influence on NIH quantified.",
      "rationale": "One-at-a-time sensitivity analysis performed for blood viscosity (±10%), hematocrit (30–36%), and Giersiepen-Wurzinger constants (published uncertainty ranges). NIH sensitivity to viscosity: 4.2%; to hematocrit: 3.8%; to damage constants: 11.3%. Dominant uncertainty source documented. Required level met."
    },
