      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Formal mapping between validation experiment input parameters and COU boundary conditions must be documented, with any discrepancies quantified and their impact on QoI bounded.",
      "rationale": "The validation experiments were conducted using the identical pump hardware and operating fluid as the COU configuration. The assessment team judged that a formal equivalency mapping is therefore unnecessary because no discrepancies exist between validation and COU input parameters. Accordingly, this factor was not carried through the structured assessment process. Note: this rationale would support a factorStatus of 'not-applicable'; however, the factor has not been formally adjudicated under the ASME V&V 40 equivalency assessment procedure, and no documented equivalency matrix exists in the evidence package. The factor therefore remains not-assessed rather than not-applicable, leaving an unresolved credibility gap at MRL 3."
    }
